        <td bgcolor="dimgray" valign="top">
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">
        
		<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=485">
        	
		<font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><b>neekorpolis</a>
        </b></font>

        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>Zombie</small></font>

        <br><img src=icon_star_purple.gif border=0><img src=icon_star_purple.gif border=0>
        <br>
        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>USA</small></font>
        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>203 Posts</small></font></td>
        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/14/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 06:46:44</font>

        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=485"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=485')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=7077&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=An+example+of+letters+sent+to+VI+that+get+ignored"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">The following is one of many letters I have sent to VI.  Not once have I have received a response.  Not once prior to the removal of the boards did I receive a response.</P><P>In short, a well written polite response does not garner a response.</P><P>The only responses I've seen are either<BR>A. We didn't break anything, get lost<BR>B. Necros are too powerful<BR>C. We'll have to fix lich before anything else, even though lich was changed to give more mana after PvP changes put in<BR>D. Your 49 pets are overpowered, even though we have nerfed them at least 5 times</P><P><BR>Anyway, here goes.  Enjoy.</P><P><BR>Dear Sir or Madam</P><P>I have been an Everquest player for over 2 years now and still find the game quite enjoyable as there is an amazing amount of content I still have yet to do.  However, I am writing because I feel that my favorite class has not received the balancing that was promised prior to the public boards changed to what they are today.  I’m sure that staffing has changed as programmers get moved to the new project leaving a few behind to manage issues.  This last patch shows that issues are slowly being resolved.  Of course the class I’m discussing is the necromancer.</P><P>With the last patch finally the necro spell Screaming terror is being overwritten by all enchanter spells since all of them are superior in duration.  Congrats.  This only took over a year and a half to be implemented.</P><P>Then I also see that the 59 pet is now immune to fear. This is good, but I will get to this in a minute.</P><P>If you will bear with me, I would like to give you a history of the necro and things that I know due to the years of playing.</P><P>When you start the game and look at the various classes you will note that the necromancer is the only class that regardless of race or god, it is given an extreme difficulty level.  Other classes can be made harder, but that is due to religion or race, not class.  Now if one were to infer that risk equals reward, one might think the necro is amazing at the end of the game.  I will get to that in a minute also. </P><P>Now, these are the things that make the necro class extreme difficulty.<BR>1.	Forever farming bone chips.  No other class in game is required to kill mobs for reagents to spells.  None.<BR>2.	Hated.  No other class is so hated.  Yes, races are, but they receive bonuses for being so hated.<BR>3.	Difficulty in obtaining needed spells.  Due to the hatred, gnomes and humans must travel to neriak to obtain spells of cleric and mage/wizard vendors as they are dubious or worse in their hometowns.  No other class has this problem short of enchanters.  But enchanters can easily remedy this with their own unique skills.<BR>4.	Losing experience when soloing if pet does more than 50% damage.  This makes the leveling process incredibly longer of a class which is well suited to soloing.</P><P>Now, these are things that are not what one would call extreme difficulty, rather hard to swallow and feeling like punishment.<BR>1.	Summon corpse – Reagents for this spell are incredibly expensive – No other class come close, although it can be argued that clerics/chanters go through gems like mad.<BR>2.	Also, reagents are only located off 3 vendors in game.  No other class has such limited location of vendors.  For a spell that is supposed to help the “group friendliness” of a class, this is an extreme disadvantage.  Not to mention such a heavy, non stackable and limiting reagent.   Until 57 or acquiring the quest robe that is.<BR>3.	Essence emeralds.  No one comes close to the sheer insanity of this concept.  Necros do not get a rez, they get an xp transfer.  Paladins get a rez that merely costs mana.  Clerics get a rez that either costs mana or a click of an epic.  If these were merely no drop and required, not consumed, they would make a lot of sense.  The insta mana spell has a large charge up time (10 minutes) and the 60 nuke has the largest recast time of any nuke in game (15 minutes).<BR>4.	Time of day restrictions on 50+ spells.  One of which is an upgraded harmshield, the other an in zone teleport.  No other class has this.   <BR>5.	Class is given debuffs that never stick or if they do, do nothing to reduce the resist rates of disease spells.  Granted we are not a buffing class, so how can we be a debuffing class.<BR>6.	DMF is wanted in zones in which it is not allowed.  This is incredibly frustrating.<BR>7.	Root stacks with snare.  Great.  But then pets are given a proc lifetap which is a trivial heal, but a wonderful root breaker.<BR>8.	Being reminded of Lich.  The PvP changes were implemented and then one month later Lich was changed to INCREASE the amount of mana it gives.  This is unacceptable to be told this has to be “fixed”.   Also the same PvP results in necro heal spells only healing 66% </P><P>Necros are a jack of all trades and master of none.  It’s part of the price they pay.  However, their upgrades are lacking 50+.  Up until 50 they are incredibly versatile and well balanced I think.  This is an evolving game, but the tragedy is that 50+ the necro evolves from an offensive class to a support class.  And what’s worse is that the necro is not very good at it. </P><P>So, in the hopes that things can change, and that the necro class was never balanced as promised,  the following is a list of requested changes and reasoning for said changes<BR>1.	50+ lifetaps returned to a lure state.  The necro’s entire set of capabilities revolves around its ability to heal itself.  Removing this capability cripples the class.  This is balanced in the fact of how little damage it does.  Compared to the nuke capabilities of all other casters they are able to do twice the damage a necro can. <BR>2.	Change the effect on the Necro POG/quest pants.  It is the 49 necro pet buff.  Not the 55<BR>3.	Coffins be sold at every necro/sk vendor location.  Also cut cost of said reagents to 5pp and 10pp<BR>4.	Receive the upgraded Feign death that the SKs receive.  Necros are the parent class and yet do not have this spell.<BR>5.	50+ pets summoning level corrected.  All previous pet spells would, at their worst, summon the best pet of the previous level.  The trend established by all previous pet spells does not continue correctly.  Compare at 39 get a pet at a minimum 6 levels below you.  At 44 get a pet 7 levels below you.  At 49 get a pet at 8 levels below you.  At 53, 10??.  At 56, 12??  At 60, 14???<BR>6.	50+ pet hps doubled at the minimum.  I understand these are “group” pets.  But necros are not masters of summoning.  The do not get to summon a pet for the correct situation.  That would be magicians.  For 52 levels a necro can count on his pet to tank for a bit, however the 53 and 56 cannot last 15 seconds before death.  Also for not being the “masters of summoning” necros pay an increased mana cost for summoning pet.  Granted doubling the 59 hps might be excessive, but it should be more since it has the same hps as the 49.<BR>7.	Max damage of 50+ pets increased.  Again a trend is set with previous pets that does not continue 50+.   For example, at 39 get a pet which can hit 6 higher.  At 44,  8 higher.  At 49, 8 higher.  At 53, 2???.  At 56,  2???  At 60, 2???     So, 10 levels of work for 6 more damage?<BR>8.	Make the 59 spectre worth it’s cost.  Yes, thank you for the unfearable spectre.  However, the magician gets this ability with a spell.  The necro pays a peridot.  No other pet caster pays a gem cost for a pet.  This pet has no damage shield.  Has no sow.  Has no incredible proc.  Does not do a respectable amount of damage.  It does not own the 49 as it should.  <BR>9.	Undead.  Necros get undead fear/charm.  The only use for them is that they cast faster and only work on said types of mobs.  Why not make undead resistant to normal fear/charm?  This would give the necro a unique ability and make necro pets unique as they are undead also.<BR>10.	Magicians receiving a DoT in the form of a necro wishlist – 30 secs  800 damage<BR>11.	Removed Time of Day restrictions.  We are not vampires.  Not letting spells work in some zones for balance reasons I can respect.  Time of day, please.<BR>12.	Make plants in PoG be plants that defoliation can effect.  No other unique target mobs in planes have this restrictions.  Summoned only spells work on mobs that look summoned.  Undead work on Undead looking mobs.<BR>13.	Ignite/chill bones changing mob melee distance.  Makes the only DD at a necros disposal unwanted.  No problem with changing to skelly, big problem going 50 ft to 4 ft.<BR>14.	Increase ignite/chill bones damage.  Ignite bones does more damage to max at 500 at 50.  Then stops.  Then 11 levels after ignite we get chill bones which does the SAME damage?  No one else gets a spell “upgrade” that does the exact same thing.  Comparing non lifetap/undead nukes progress from 160 dd at 24, 220 at 34, 500 at 44 and 500 at 55???<BR>15.	Increase Mana transfer line 50+.  Snare gets better till 75%.  Rez to 93%.  Slow to 75%.  Haste to 75%.  Necros get mana transfer that maxes at 30%????  If we are twitchers, so be it.  Must we suck at it?<BR>16.	Make essence emerald No Drop and needed, not consumed.  Spells cost a lot of mana, take a large charge up/recharge and are properly balanced EXCEPT the consuming essence emerald<BR>17.	Decrease cast time on darkness line.  Does ensnare take 7 seconds to cast?  No.  Does it last an incredible amount of time? Yes.  Why use the darkness line?  Oh, to snare.  Should be 2.5 or less to cast<BR>18.	Decrease the cast time on Touch of Night.  Deflux owns because I might get that heal off before I’m dead.  Touch of night just takes me right back to 6 seconds again.  So, mmm, cast deflux twice or hope to get touch of night off once?<BR>19.	Change Arch Lich to some form of melee buff since we have 2 liches at 60.  Or anything creative and a reward for the ungodly amount of time it takes to get to 60<BR>20.	Provide an upgrade to Screaming Terror.  What other class depends on a level 24 spell at 60?</P><P><BR>I appreciate you taking the time to read this list and would deeply appreciate a response.  .  Should these suggestion be implemented, I feel that the necro would receive its just reward for the level of extreme difficulty and the incredible amount of time it takes to get to 60.  Also, the perceived role and reward of the 60 necro would be definable.</P><P>Right now the 60 roles are<BR>Warrior – only one who can tank with disciplines and do a good deal of melee damage<BR>Rogue – only one who can open certain doors, disarm traps and do an insane amount of damage.  Also CR<BR>Monk – insane melee damage and can single pull like no one else<BR>SK – tank somewhat, damage somewhat, decent pet, harmtouch now quite nice with discipline<BR>Paladin – tank somewhat, damage somewhat<BR>Ranger – damage greatly, control agro on self, great damage with discipline, snare<BR>Cleric – duh<BR>Druid – teleporter, buffs, DD, snare<BR>Shaman – slower, buffer, haste, DD, root<BR>Wizard -  only one who knows he can nuke, teleport, snare, root<BR>Enchanter – haste, mez, clarity, slower<BR>Bard – charm, heal, mana, buffs, haste<BR>Magician – Coth, nuke, pets, summon items, buffs<BR>Necro – twitch bitch, Dot if can.  Only caster in some situations to do Zero damage</P><P><BR> </font></td>
      </tr>

