        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Very good letter which I agree with about 90% of.  I would be very willing to sign any potential petition.</P><P>However, I doubt we'll get much joy - all these questions have been asked before and been shot down in flames with lame replies.</P><P>The PoG defoliation is just a joke - their protected by Tunare??  If Tunare's protecting them how come these sharp pointy bits of metal the meatheads are wielding damage them - surely Tunare can protect them from that too.</P><P>Coffins are a nightmare until quest/PoG robes or 57.  I had to do a huge CR once as the only summoner - we had people going to fetch the coffins to me as they could only carry 8 at a time.  And WTF 175pp/throw - people will do anything possible to try avoiding that.  How come clerics can rez for mana and summon a PC to their corpse and yet to do the reverse with no exp gain it costs us loads of mana + crazily awkward and expensive reagant.</P><P>Pets I don't see them doing anything much with - about the best we can hope for is no Peridot on 59 (a drop rate on spell increased) and maybe some HP increases on 53 and 56.</P><P>Can't understand why they won't let us land lifetaps - 300HPs is hardly overpowering and would make lots of us very happy.</P><P>ST is one way in which I can be useful to a group but we should get a higher level spell which lasts say 30 seconds.</P><P>Essence Emeralds - surely the most stupid idea ever in EQ.  WTF would anyone use one of these to cast a lifetap?  I would rather die and pay to get a cleric to rez me and then start over.  The rez effect is the only use for these and even then I doubt it has been used much as its much cheaper to get a cleric - even if you pay 100pp for the rez its still 1/10th the price of an EE.  I think this whole line of spells needs to be completely rethought as I doubt anyone really uses them.</P><P>Time of Day spells??  Whats the point of even memming them if I can only use them 1/3rd of the time?  I nice little same zone evac but hey, if I'm fighting a mob at the wrong time its no use - I might as well go with FD and hope that my non-upgraded SK version works.</P><P>Chill Bones - good to get something which uses cold rather than fire.  However, I agree for a 11 level increase to get no damage increase is just insulting.  Either lower the spell level or increase the damage.</P><P>A couple of non-mentioned points...</P><P>Darkness spell line...  Why do 90% of necros 50+ still use the 24 (I think) dooming version?  Its because its relatively quick casting even though its sucky damage.  We don't use these spells for DoTs!  We need an upgrade 50+ somewhere which can have 10 points of damage over 2 minutes for all I care as long as it casts in say 2 seconds.</P><P>On a related point, our epic is the lamest of them all.  Yes the damage is nice but the casting time is just crazy.  It should be the case that a PC with an epic should make a difference.  What difference does a necro with an epic make - bugger all.</P><P>Again, this has turned into a bitch fest and I must remember that I can solo some things other classes can only dream of.  To take down blue conning mobs solo one every 3 minutes for 5 hours solid can't be done by any other class as far as I'm aware.</P><P>It's just the little frustrations we would like fixed.</P><P>Draknn Fels, Level 53 Erudite Necromancer<BR>Divide et Impera, Bristlebane<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
